The paper deals with the construction of self-dual codes, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of λ-circulant and λ-reverse circulant matrices suggests a connection to cryptography (cs.CR). The paper also discusses weight enumerators, which are a tool used in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of codes using circulant matrices is a topic in coding theory (cs.CC). Finally, the use of extensions to obtain new codes suggests a connection to numerical analysis (cs.NA).
